/**
 * Definition for a binary tree node.
 * public class TreeNode {
 *     int val;
 *     TreeNode left;
 *     TreeNode right;
 *     TreeNode() {}
 *     TreeNode(int val) { this.val = val; }
 *     TreeNode(int val, TreeNode left, TreeNode right) {
 *         this.val = val;
 *         this.left = left;
 *         this.right = right;
 *     }
 * }
 */
class Solution {
    public List<List<Integer>> levelOrder(TreeNode root) {
        List<List<Integer>> ans = new ArrayList<List<Integer>>();
        if (root == null){
            return ans;
        }
        Queue<TreeNode> queue = new LinkedList<TreeNode>();
        queue.add(root);
        while(queue.isEmpty() == false){
            int levelsize = queue.size();
            List<Integer> level = new ArrayList<Integer>();
            for (int i = 1; i <= levelsize; i ++){
                TreeNode current = queue.remove();
                level.add(current.val);
                if (current.left != null){
                    queue.add(current.left);
                }
                if (current.right != null){
                    queue.add(current.right);
                }
            }
            ans.add(level);
        }
        return ans;
    }
}

/*
Notes:

(BFS(Breadth First Search): returning the level order traversal.)

1.	BFS(Breadth First Search): traversing in the level order.
(1)	Step1: Assigning a “queue”, and using a “While loop” to do the DFS.
(2)	Step2: Adding the root into the queue.
(3)	Step3: Using a “for loop” to iterate all the value in the queue. For each value, removing the value and adding its child immediately. 
(4)	Step4: After the “for loop”, we had already put all the values on same level into the queue, so we can output our temporary result.
(5)	Step5: Ending the “While” if there is no element in the queue anymore.

2.	Queue: 
(1)	add() - Inserts the specified element into the queue. If the task is successful, add() returns true, if not it throws an exception.
(2)	offer() - Inserts the specified element into the queue. If the task is successful, offer() returns true, if not it returns false.
(3)	element() - Returns the head of the queue. Throws an exception if the queue is empty.
(4)	peek() - Returns the head of the queue. Returns null if the queue is empty.
(5)	remove() - Returns and removes the head of the queue. Throws an exception if the queue is empty.
(6)	poll() - Returns and removes the head of the queue. Returns null if the queue is empty.

*/
